g.text: Stage 3 - Pair the Smart Key:
1. Navigate to Diagnostics.
2. Press the motorcycle's Power ON/OFF button (Note: the motorcycle will not appear to power ON).
3. Within 10 seconds, click Immobiliser/Keyless ECM Diagnostics.
4. Pair the smart key using the Add New Key function.
5. Press the button on the smart key after it has been successfully paired.
Stage 4 - Pair the Engine ECM with the Immobiliser:
1. Make sure the smart key is in range and press the Power ON/OFF button. The instruments and headlight should now turn ON.
2. Switch the engine start/stop switch to the RUN position.
3. Navigate to Immobiliser/Keyless ECM Diagnostics and pair the engine ECM and immobiliser.
Stage 8 - Final Steps:
1. Turn the ignition off for at least 60 seconds.
2. Check the ignition can be turned ON and engine started using each key.
3. Check all ECMs for stored DTCs and erase as necessary.
4. If fitted, set up the tyre pressure monitoring system as described in the Triumph Diagnostic Tool User Guide.
Stage 7 - Reconnect and Pair the Electronic Steering Lock (if fitted).
1. Connect the electronic steering lock as described in the prcedure below.
2. Navigate to Immobiliser/Keyless ECM Diagnostics and pair the Electronic Steering Lock.
Stage 1 - Preliminary steps:
1. Install the replacement keyless ECM.
2. Disconnect the Electronic Steering Lock as descibed above.
3. Reconnect the battery.
4. Make sure you have all the new keys ready.
5. Connect the diagnostic tool.
Stage 2 - Partial Keyless ECM download:
1. Select the correct Keyless ECM calibration for download using Manual Model Selection.
2. Do not click Confirm to start the download at this point.
3. Press the motorcycle's Power ON/OFF button (Note: the motorcycle will not appear to power ON).
4. Within 10 seconds, click Confirm to start the download.
5. Follow all on-screen instructions during the download.
6. Click Finish when download has completed.
Stage 6 - Full Keyless ECM download:
1. Navigate to Immobiliser/Keyless ECM download.
2. Use Automatic Model Selection to complete a full keyless ECM download.
3. Make sure the correct model is detected and select the correct calibration for your region.
3. Follow all on-screen instructions during the download.
4. Click Finish when the download has completed.
Stage 5 - Pair the Passive Keys:
1. Pair the passive key using the Add New Key function.
